40|$|What {{does the}} general public know about <b>banking</b> <b>supervision?</b> What {{objectives}} does the public think bank supervisors should pursue? We investigate these issues using a survey among Dutch households. First, {{we find that the}} public's knowledge about <b>banking</b> <b>supervision</b> is far from perfect. We also find that respondents often expect more from supervisors than they can realistically achieve. Finally, our findings suggest that better - informed people have more realistic views on <b>banking</b> <b>supervision.</b> Realistic views on <b>banking</b> <b>supervision</b> lead to more prudent financial behaviour, which, in turn, contributes to financial stability. Therefore, the communication policies of banking supervisors should aim to improve the public's knowledge about <b>banking</b> <b>supervision.</b> <b>banking</b> <b>supervision,</b> knowledge; communication; financial literacy; household decisionmaking...|$|R
